Subject: [PATCH 2/3] eink: add screensaver enable + opacity preferences

Adds two new entries to the Settings > Display > E-Ink Display screen
under a new "Screensaver" category:

  - eink_pref_screensaver_enabled (SwitchPreferenceCompat, default on):
    backed by Settings.System.eink_screensaver_enabled, which gates the
    framework-side dream trigger in PhoneWindowManager.startedGoingToSleep.

  - eink_pref_screensaver_alpha (StepperPreference, default 100):
    backed by Settings.System.eink_screensaver_alpha, read by
    EinkDreamService to set the moon-Zzz background opacity.

Both prefs are persisted directly to Settings.System; no AIDL roundtrip
is needed since these are display-side controls, not hardware controls.

